description: Manage rewrite rule sets of an application gateway.

commands.name: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set create
commands.syntax:
az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set create --gateway-name
                                                       --name
                                                       --resource-group
                                                       [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                       [--rules]
examples: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set create --gateway-name MyGateway --name MyRewriteRuleSet --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set delete
commands.syntax:
az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set delete --gateway-name
                                                       --name
                                                       --resource-group
                                                       [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
examples: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set delete -g MyResourceGroup --gateway-name MyGateway -n MyRuleSet

commands.name: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set list
commands.syntax:
az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set list --gateway-name
                                                     --resource-group
examples: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set list --gateway-name MyGateway --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set show
commands.summary: Get the details of a rewrite rule set.
commands.syntax:
az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set show --gateway-name
                                                     --name
                                                     --resource-group
examples: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set show --gateway-name MyGateway --name MyRewriteRuleSet --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set update
commands.syntax:
az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set update --gateway-name
                                                       --name
                                                       --resource-group
                                                       [--add]
                                                       [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                       [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                       [--remove]
                                                       [--rules]
                                                       [--set]
examples: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set update --gateway-name MyGateway --name MyRewriteRuleSet --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
commands.syntax:
az network application-gateway rewrite-rule set wait [--created]
                                                     [--custom]
                                                     [--deleted]
                                                     [--exists]
                                                     [--gateway-name]
                                                     [--ids]
                                                     [--interval]
                                                     [--resource-group]
                                                     [--subscription]
                                                     [--timeout]
                                                     [--updated]
